07/09/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- The government decided on Thursday (September 6th) to downsize public administration by 5,015 people, according to Balkanweb. 
By far, the largest cuts will be in the interior ministry -- 2,909 civil servants -- with 833 cut from the education ministry and 455 at the Academy of Science.
In other news, Albania's 10th contingent of peacekeeping troops left on Thursday for Iraq. 
At the send-off ceremony, Prime Minister Sali Berisha said Albania is determined to be right where NATO is. 
(Kohajone, Gazeta Shqiptare, Korrier, Shekulli - 07/09/07; Balkanweb, Albanian Prime Minister's web site - 06/09/07)
